Pacific islanders have denied claims that a missing German tourist was eaten by cannibals after insisting: 'We prefer hot dogs to people'.

Fears that German traveller Stefan Ramin had been cooked and devoured erupted after his charred remains were found on a campfire on the French Polynesian island of Nuku Hiva.

The horrific discovery was made last week by police hunting for 40-year-old Ramin and local hunter Henri Haiti after they failed to return from a jungle expedition.

